The paper discusses quantitative approaches to determine the cognitive distance between evaluators and evaluees based on the journals they have published in. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of computer science related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), computers and society (cs.CY), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
